<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="311" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,426,955]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,498,523]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[333,575,499,523]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Stenoloba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albistriata">
<emphasis box="[333,575,499,523]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Stenoloba albistriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[594,679,498,523]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–30" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1839,1862]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,193,1818]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 16–30. Stenoloba spp., adult. 16. S. albistriata, female, slide HHL-6182-2; 17. S. brunnescens, male, slide HHL- 6140-1; 18. S. rectilinea, male, slide HHL-6135-1; 19. S. acutivalva, female, slide HHL-6144-2; 20. S. motuoensis, female, slide HHL-2924-2; 21. S. speideli, female, slide HHL-6148-2; 22. S. glaucescens, male, slide HHL-2455-1; 23. Ditto, female, slide HHL-3185-2; 24. S. nora, male, slide HHL-6166-1; 25. Ditto, female, slide HHL-6167-2; 26. S. plumbeoculata, female, slide HHL-6164-2; 27. S. viridicollar, male, slide HHL-6517-1; 28. S. basiviridis, male, slide HHL-6175-1; 29. S. pulla, male, slide HHL-3179-1; 30. S. dominula, male, slide HHL-6169-2 [all materials from coll. NEFU]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1188561/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) is a typical member of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wileman" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[1018,1151,499,523]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Stenoloba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olivacea">
<emphasis box="[1018,1032,499,522]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1049,1151,499,523]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">olivacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group, differing externally from the related species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wileman" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[564,695,534,558]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Stenoloba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olivacea">
<emphasis box="[564,578,535,558]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[593,695,534,558]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">olivacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kononenko &amp; Ronkay" authorityYear="1998" box="[711,855,534,558]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Stenoloba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fontinalis">
<emphasis box="[711,725,535,558]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[740,855,534,558]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">fontinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ronkay" authorityYear="2001" box="[872,1010,534,558]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Stenoloba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="benedeki">
<emphasis box="[872,887,535,558]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[903,1010,534,558]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">benedeki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pekarsky &amp; Saldatis" authorityYear="2013" box="[1026,1140,534,558]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Stenoloba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solaris">
<emphasis box="[1026,1040,535,558]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1058,1140,534,558]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">solaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pekarsky, Dvorak &amp; G. Ronkay" authorityYear="2013" box="[1201,1356,534,558]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Stenoloba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subsolaris">
<emphasis box="[1201,1215,535,558]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1232,1356,534,558]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">subsolaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by its smaller size; the presence of strong reddish brown spots at base of forewing, but missing of red spot in the reniform; the conspicuous, white-filled, sinuous ante- and postmedial crosslines bordering the broad medial area; the well-discernible, wide, dark medial stripe; the relatively distinct, sinuous transverse line of the hindwing. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[522,669,678,702]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Stenoloba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albistriata">
<emphasis box="[522,536,679,702]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[550,669,678,702]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">albistriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation box="[842,1165,678,703]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" refId="ref15624" refString="Kononenko, V. S. &amp; Ronkay, L. (2000) A revision of the genus Stenoloba Staudinger, 1892 (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae, Bryophilinae) with description of 25 new species and 3 new subspecies from East Asia (I). Insecta Koreana, 17 (3), 137 - 174." type="journal article">Kononenko &amp; Ronkay 2000</bibRefCitation>
) differ from those of its allied species by their narrower valva, shorter and narrower the uncus, and shape of the aedeagus and vesica. The female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[355,439,750,775]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–57" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1839,1862]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,205,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,193,1818]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 48–57. Stenoloba spp., female genitalia. 48. S. huanxipoa sp. n., paratype, slide HHL-3176-2; 49. S. acontioides sp. n., holotype, slide HHL-6185-2; 50. S. assimilina sp. n., paratype, slide HHL-3853-2; 51. S. albistriata, slide HHL-6182-2; 52. S. acutivalva, slide HHL-6144-2; 53. S. motuoensis, slide HHL-2924-2; 54. S. speideli, slide HHL-6148-2; 55. S. glaucescens, slide HHL-3185-2; 56. S. nora, slide HHL-6167-2; 57. S. plumbeoculata, slide HHL-6164-2 [all materials from coll. NEFU]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1188571/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
) differ from known of those the related taxa by the presence of a heavily sclerotised crest in the lateral part of the cervix bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="311" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,426,955]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,822,847]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Distribution.</emphasis>
Southwest 
<collectingCountry box="[488,555,822,847]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">China</collectingCountry>
(Prov. 
<collectingRegion box="[642,732,823,847]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
), north 
<collectingCountry box="[822,933,823,847]" name="Myanmar" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
. Two females were collected in April. First record for 
<collectingCountry box="[281,351,858,883]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">China</collectingCountry>
. The species formerly was known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[906,1017,859,883]" name="Myanmar" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
. New data considerable extend the distribution pattern of 
<taxonomicName box="[402,547,894,918]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Stenoloba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albistriata">
<emphasis box="[402,416,895,918]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[430,547,894,918]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">albistriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,426,955]" box="[199,1251,930,955]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,930,955]" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Notes.</emphasis>
The female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[547,692,931,955]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Stenoloba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="311" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albistriata">
<emphasis box="[547,561,931,954]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[575,692,931,955]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">albistriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is described and illustrated here for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
